reviews: Pavillon de la Reine ranks as one of my favorite hotels in the world. It is located in the heart of the Marais on the Place des Voges and all Paris is at your feet and yet, when you walk through the entrance, you are in a little haven of quiet beauty and comfort in a courtyard facing a 16th century building that has been redone with exquisite taste. The service is professional and personal without ever being obtrusive. We stayed in a suite with a small comfortable living room and an ample bedroom with a kingsize bed. The bathroom was luxurious, marble, double sinks, large walk in shower and large tub and heated floors, the linens and accessories top of the line. Our tall windows overlooked the beautiful courtyard. Breakfast was included and, in addition to the opulent cold and hot buffet, there was a menu to fit personal tastes. Food options throughout the day were delicious. The most distinguishing feature remains the warmth and excellence of the service, from its incredible management team to its housekeeping. A perfect hatel in a perfect setting. We wouldn't stay anywhere else.

Excellent hotel in a historic area of Le Marais. Attentive check in and explanation of the room. Great location and base for touring. 20 minutes walk to Notre Dame. Pretty room and a little noisy from the street. Original beams and beautifully appointed bathroom. Good breakfast. Go and enjoy this grand hotel steeped in history. Great base for local amenities as well.

In short – this is the most lovely place I've ever stayed. Everything was absolutely outstanding. The location. The ambiance. The room. The service. Just world class. It's the kind of place that stays with you. That you wish you had a permanent residence in. It – like the city it's located in – is simply magic.

What a magical boutique hotel. Located right on the Place des Vosges in the heart of Le Marais, it was steps from a wonderful brasserie and an Amorino gelato location and easy Uber rides to wherever we wished to go.

We were warmly welcomed and helped to our room -- a lushly decorated and spacious suite with a living room, bedroom, walk-in wardrobe and huge, fabulous bathroom. Actually, the entire property is lushly decorated. Both the bar and restaurant (on opposite sides of the lobby) were warm, comfy, lux, elegant, old-world, hip and modern all at once. We had drinks in the lounge both nights of our stay, enjoyed the breakfast buffet each morning in the restaurant and sampled the fare one night for dinner. Everything was excellent.

Special shout-out to the wonderful concierge who arranged last-minute museum tickets for us with, seemingly, a snap of his fingers.

This hotel is the perfect, secret hideaway when the hustle and bustle of larger hotels is not the vibe you are going for. Like others at the hotel lounge we met, this will be our go-to hotel in Paris from now on.

We traveled to France for our Christmas vacation this year and stayed in many different hotels. There were several aspects of each hotel we stayed at that we paid the most attention to, therefore I made the decision to rate them all.
This was my favorite hotel during the entire trip. Although it is located in a different part of the city than where we have previously been, we truly like it. Nearby eateries abound, getting to Notre Dame is simple, and the area is peaceful at night.

Everything was perfect! We were upgraded to a huge suite and welcomed with flowers, chocolates & a bottle of wine. The location on the Place des Vosges can't be beat - lots of shops & restaurants nearby. Breakfast had sweet & savory sections and was served in the cozy front rooms. Service was outstanding. Rudy got us a reservation at Miss Ko - so fun! We loved our stay.

This was our first post Covid trip and were looking forward to a return visit to the Pavillon de la Reine. We have been staying here for several visits to Paris and it is our all-time Favorite. Our suite was very comfortable with a beautiful bouquet of flowers and a large orchid in the living room. It was overlooking the front garden and even though it was close to the elevator was very quiet.

The staff, as usual, was very welcoming and helpful for our stay. I had the concierge (Rudy) make all our dinner reservation before we arrived. He was very helpful with suggestions and I feel that we received very good tables as a result.

We will look forward to our next visit to Paris and we will definitely stay in our Home away from Home, the Pavillon de la Reine.

For our Christmas holidays this year, we took a trip to France and stayed in a variety of hotels, 7 in total. As we moved from hotel to hotel, there were certain things we focused on the most so I decided to rate them at each hotel.

Bathroom (whether had a shower) – very nicely equipped bathrooms, some had the toilet separate, some did not. A super nice shower which you do not always see in France.
Lobby – small but nice, with a fabulous courtyard that is all lit up
Location in the city or town – good location, on a very nice square in the city (called the pink square because of the color of the stone used in the buildings there)
Size of room – generous in size
Breakfast – good
Elevator (was there one?) – yes
Ambiance - Delightful. The rooms are so beautifully decorated. We will stay here again when we return to Paris. We loved the entire experience here.

Of all the places we stayed this trip, this was my favorite. It is in a different area of the city than we have stayed in before, but we really liked it. Lots of restaurants around, an easy walk to Notre Dame, and quieter at night.

This hotel is terrible. The clientele was pretty lacking in taste, and most of the staff give off the vibe that they either don’t want to be working there, or don’t know what they’re doing. I have stayed at many 5-star hotels around the world and this is by far the worst. The interior is dated, and did not reflect the level of cleanliness or functionality expected for the price. Concierge, housekeeping, and room service are awful. Would not recommend this place to anyone; don’t be fooled by the nice picture of the outside of the hotel. One star for decent location. Trust—there are significantly better hotels in Paris for the same price.

What a great hotel!! Everything was excellent!! The staff was excellent, and professional!!!

Singa- Bellman

Prahpahn- waiter (spelling)

Biju- Waiter

Rudy- Clefs D'Or

Henree- front desk

Eloise- front desk

Bondugu- Evening server

L'edie Jane- evening server/supervisor

Made our 20th Anniversary celebration wonderful!!

One thing to note though, depending on what type of package you purchase with the hotel, your breakfast may not be included. While it is a really full and delicious breakfast, it does run €30 if it's not included in your package.

Perfectly located in Place de Voges, Le Pavillion de la Reine did not disappoint. The front desk team were very friendly, welcoming, and gave us many excellent dining recommendations. The beautiful courtyard was an excellent place for breakfast or an afternoon drink. Breakfast was included in with our room package and was served in the lobby or if preferred in your room. Speaking of the rooms. We stayed in a junior suite. We appreciated the ample closet space and split bathroom/toilet. There was lots of natural light on the 3rd floor facing Rue de Bearn.

Bottom line: Welcoming, understated luxury, stylish with thoughtfully appointed rooms, and fantastic staff. Conveniently located in the Marais. Highly recommended!

This boutique hotel had great rooms, comfortable beds and the best staff. They were so friendly and so helpful. The concierges gave us the best restaurant recommendations. The Marais neighborhood had everything to offer. Great food, amazing shopping and small museums. You literally could stay just in the neighborhood for days and not get board. Paris is also a great walkable City. We did 29000 steps each day. We cannot wait to go back!

This hotel is directly on the Place Des Vosges, as excellent a location as exists in Paris. Everything about the hotel speaks luxury and it delivers from stylish rooms to a superb breakfast. Of special note is Clementine, the Reservation Manager. My wife forgot to pack an important item when we checked out and when discovered at our next stop we called the hotel. A DHL package was delivered to us at our following stop and our trip was able to continue as planned. Cheers for Clementine!

We booked a last minute stay at this hotel when our flight was delayed on a layover at CDG. We visit Paris often and have stayed in many or Paris’ finest hotels and we will definitely be come back here. Why? First, the location — it’s hard to think of a better location than ON Place des Vosges. Second, the property is gorgeous —- incredible courtyard, beautifully decorated common areas that are begging to be used to read a book or have a cocktail between sightseeing, and our suite was tres large, particularly for Paris standards! Lastly, the hotel staff was incredible — they went out of their way to ensure we had everything we needed during our short stay and coordinated our dinner reservation. A really wonderful spot — we’ll no doubt be back.

So much to love about Le Pavillon de la Reine--its regal beauty, graciousness, location, superb food & wine, excellent staff. Behind its vaulted entry on the Place des Vosges, the Pavillon welcomes you with its serenity and grace. The reception staff will book you efficiently but also solve any and all problems that might arise (Paolo was especially kind and resourceful). Each of the 56 rooms and suites is different, and you might want to specify whether you prefer modern or traditional decor. Rooms a bit small. The breakfast buffet offers fresh orange juice, fruit, yoghurt, and croissants, but you can also order eggs exactly as you like them. My easy-over eggs arrived perfectly prepared & utterly delicious. After our exhausting days spent exploring the Marais and its many shops and museums, we would return for marvelous wine, cheese, and charcuterie in the garden. We missed the afternoon tea, although friends say it's worth returning for the experience.

Pros:
-beautiful and romantic hotel
-well situated in the marais
-nice size and intimate
-we had a beautiful suite (Rimbaud) with two bathrooms (one windowed), a separate toilet room, a living room, bedroom and large walk in closet

Cons:
-staff are nice but not great: there is no follow up. Some examples: The morning of our arrival we were told we would get a text around 10:30 am alerting us if our room was ready. We walked back around 1 pm and still no text.
-we asked for a late checkout and were told to ask the night before. The night before we were told to call first thing in the morning. At this point it would have been nice to offer to just call us back.
-I am referring to the staff at the front desk who don’t go much beyond ‘hello’ in terms of interaction w guests. The person who was the most personable and friendly was the doorman.

Located in the very cosmopolitan district of Le Marais and within the Place des Vosges, this is a beautifully charming Parisian boutique hotel.

The entrance to the hotel is what you envisage every Parisian hotel should look like. The hotel is tastefully decorated, with a stylish lounge that doubles as the breakfast and evening dining room, along with the library and outdoor terrace. It was so enjoyable to sit in the terrace as the sun sets for aperitifs or a digestive in the evening, or just to have breakfast or dinner.

We had breakfast at the hotel on every morning of our stay, which was enjoyable. Breakfast consisted of a buffet selection, and cooked eggs were also on offer, and cooked to your liking (scrambled, omelette), along with freshly brewed tea and coffee which was brought to your table.

We booked a superior room, which was a reasonable size that overlooked a gorgeous courtyard garden, and the bathroom is off the bedroom, as is the separate toilet. To access the shower in the bathroom you have to step into the deep bath which was a little awkward to step into, and the shower/bath had a privacy and shower curtain, which I don’t particularly like.

The entrance between the bedroom, bathroom and toilet is also very narrow.

The bed and pillows were comfortable, the room had in-room air conditioning, safe and tea and coffee making facilities. I thought the bedroom furniture was quite dark and looked tired, and not really the antique style or the French provincial style I was personally expecting in a boutique hotel. The hotel has a lift, although quite tiny, however that’s not unusual for European boutique hotels.

The staff were friendly, engaging and very helpful and most spoke English (as a second language), which helped us immensely.

The hotel is opposite the Place des Vosges and surrounded by cafes, restaurants, bars, boutique art galleries and several smaller museums, along with Victor Hugo's house which is only a 2-min walk from the hotel, all worth visiting.

The streets in and around the hotel were a joy to meander in and there is so much history in the area to enjoy. The hotel is a short walk to the Seine River and about a 20 minute taxi drive to the Eiffel Tower or the city centre of Paris.

Highly recommend Le Pavillon de la Reine

Although the hotel looks nice from the outside, the rooms are very dark and quite run down.
The service is nice although they refused us a table for lunch even though we were guests of the hotel.
The worst thing is the strong smell of urine everywhere outside the hotel. A smell that we could smell even when inside our room.
It's a pity that the city doesn't take better care of the cleanliness. You expect better than this when you pay 700 Eur per night. We'll not be back.

A lovely hotel in a prime spot right on the Place des Vosges square and right in the popular Marais district, it’s spread over about four floors with a pleasant and attractive courtyard at the front. Staff were all very pleasant and helpful. Our room wasn’t ready when we arrived unfortunately, but we were quite early and it was long before check-in time, so that’s hardly their fault. We were though asked if we would like to take a shower in the spa changing rooms which I thought was a nice touch. I was a bit surprised when we returned later that our bags weren’t already in the room instead of having to ask for them. A minor point I know, but this is a 5* hotel.

The room itself was perhaps rather optimistically described as a suite. Perhaps the fact that you walk in to a small hallway with the bedroom and bathroom off of here rather than directly in to the bedroom is what constitutes a suite. Again, perhaps I’m being picky, but for €700 a night I thought an extra lounge area might have been included. That said, it was a decent enough sized room although no view other than the office block opposite. Facilities included a Nespresso machine and a mini-bar although if you wanted anything other than coffee (tea, for example) you were out of luck. There was also a TV on the wall, although we didn’t use this so I don’t know what the picture quality was like, and a safe. The bed was large and comfy whilst the bathroom had twin sinks and a separate walk-in shower and bath. The shower was ok, certainly hot enough, but could have been a little more powerful. A couple of bottles of complementary water were provided, although the turn-down service was ridiculously early some days. They knocked on the door at 5:30pm when we had obviously yet to go out for the evening, and didn’t return later. I thought the sockets might have included USB chargers, but no such luck and it was quite difficult to find a socket that was actually liv e all the time instead of going off with the lights. In the end I had to scramble around under the desk to find one. There was no noise to speak of from outside as we were on a quiet side street, but the internal walls did seem a little thin. Fortunately our neighbours were fairly quiet.

Breakfast was a help yourself buffet selection, although we were also offered cooked egg dishes such as omelettes. There was a good selection that covered most bases, including hot food (sausages, crispy bacon, scrabbled egg and something that looked rather like ratatouille), a good selection of cold meats and cheeses, smoked salmon, cereals, yoghurts, pastries, fruit and nuts. I can’t really think of anything else that I would have added. The croissants were exceptionally good, but everything else was very nice too.

Overall, a lovely hotel in a great spot and I’d happily stay here again.

What an outstanding place. Beautiful. Impeccable service. Meticulous attention to detail and all in a non-pretentious package.

Probably the best hotel I have ever stayed in.

From the arrival experience (thanks for the balloons, champagne and chocolate for my girlfriend’s birthday) to the helpfulness of the concierge to the service at breakfast to the lovely ‘honour bar’ - absolutely immaculate.

And a fantastic location to boot.

I would give it 6 stars if I could.

This is a truly 5 star hotel in a great location in Paris. A very comfortable, clean and spacious room, with a large comfortable bed. The concierge staff are very helpful, with very good English. Has a great casual bar with good range of drinks and snack food. Highly recommend.

This hotel is located in Place des Vosges, previously a beautiful old mansion. It is quiet and has a wonderful courtyard where you can eat outside for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Service is top notch and very friendly and helpful. However, the room is uncomfortable. It was very dark, and the mattress was extremely hard and uncomfortable.

Located on the Place des Voges, this property is wonderful. Loved the neighborhood for its quaintness and quiet. At the same time, it's close to multiple Metro stops/lines which made navigating the city quite easy. Breakfast was included (and was delicious). The rooms, while small, are well-equipped and maid service was prompt and thorough. The courtyard is a wonderful space any time of day -- for breakfast or afternoon wine/snack. Service was on point. They also offer airport transfers (for additional fee of course). This was our first visit and if we return to Paris, we'll be back here. Cannot recommend highly enough.

This is a uniquely charming hotel. The decor is elegant country. The staff is warm, respectful and engaging. The breakfast is delicious. The spa is very good. The feeling is like being at home. I highly recommend Le Pavillon de la Reine.

A perfect Parisian getaway! My partner and I stayed for four nights for our honeymoon and could not have been better looked after. From the impeccable service to the beautiful and very comfortable rooms, through to the delicious food in restaurant Anne, we could not have had a better or more special stay.

Lovely hotel, lovely location, lovely staff. Warm,friendly, helpful staff really make this beautiful place the perfect place to stay in Paris. It’s a glorious building in a glorious location but the standout is the wonderful staff.

This hotel is a beautiful hidden gem in one of Paris' most gorgeous areas (La Marais). Not only is the location fantastic and walking distance twosome of the best cafes, restaurants, patisseries, and ice cream spots, but the hotel itself is absolutely beautiful. Sitting in the courtyard sipping on a glass of rose was probably one of my most memorable moments during my solo Parisian trip. The breakfast was delicious with an abundance of options. The room, wow. I had asked for a room with a view and was given a room with three views; over looking some of Paris' most beautiful architecture, quaint streets, and overlooking the courtyard. I will be coming back again!

We stayed at this lovely hotel for a week. It was extremely busy but the staff were so professional and focused on the well being of their guests. The concierge staff were constantly bombarded with requests and handled everything magnificently. The night concierge staff had found us restaurant reservations prior to our visit and every one was excellent. The food at the hotel was exquisite and the courtyard elegant and welcoming. Our room was very well air conditioned which turned out to be such a blessing because of the high temperatures in Paris that week. The bed was large a very comfortable and I am very particular about beds.

This is my favourite hotel in Paris - in the Place des Vosges, which is a beautiful square in the Marais. I have been coming to this hotel for years, and I feel very at home every time I return. The Place des Vosges is architecturally sublime, and the hotel,is tucked away in its own lovely courtyard which is a real sum trap on a sunny day.. Service is outstanding, the rooms are beautiful and well equipped, the food is excellent - what more can I say?

Bad experience! Confusion with my reservation and payment through a their party travel website. Vanessa at the hotel is just flat out dishonest! My room smelled like a dead hamster! Slow wifi, big gap under the front door so anything that happens in the hall you hear everything, snobby staff who don't want to be bothered dealing with fundamental issues. Was over charged and the curreny exchange rate they gave me was a absolute ripoff. Two nights was too long in this property.

Very professional and welcoming staff. We enjoyed breakfast in the dining room and drinks in the courtyard. Rooms are quiet and well done. Location is great for exploring the Marais area and close to the metro stop
I will stay here again

This is a very good hotel in a great area, the Marais, with plenty to see and do within walking distance. Extremely friendly staff, our suite was very spacious and immaculate. The breakfast was fantastic. Such a perfect hotel for a stay in Paris!

I can't praise this hotel and staff highly enough. This is our 3rd trip to Paris and we always try to stay in a different area.
Our room was lovely (room 52), so clean and spacious for Paris. The breakfast was delicious and such good quality. We have stayed in 5 star hotels all over the world and are very fussy.
The concierges recommended two great brasseries in the neighbourhood and were very knowledgeable. All the staff were so great and I work in hospitality myself.
Well done guys.

The hotel is situated behind a courtyard leading off the Place des Vosges. It is simply lovely. The staff were excellent. We had a double height corner room with a bed on the higher level. Champagne on arrival. Very comfortable public areas. Great breakfasts. We were made very welcome. Ideal for persons looking for a gracious, relaxing stay. Highly recommended.

Service was great and its location Is fantastic. All was good. Highly recommended !
Restaurant was excellent, very nice terrace and little garden. Decoration was very stylish. If you are looking for a quite and luxury hotel, you just found it

The most romantic and calm place to stay in Paris at the beautiful Place des Vosges. The staff is great, concierge arranges everything you might need, from dinner reservations, bike rental and transfers. The most tranquil way to get around. A must stay place. Even Parisians love it and they should know.

It's a fabulous hotel, seeming more like a home , with beauty, sophistication, and welcoming....The interior park, with plants, trees, orchids, and even sculpture is divine. It's fun to sit in the garden with friends, or just alone, imbibing Paris, sipping cafe, and reading a book.

It is so rare that you search for a vision that you have had of a hotel that you not only get what you are looking for but far exceed your vision but PDLR did exactly that. When you walk off the Square at Place De La Vosges and enter the courtyard you just know you have arrived at something special. The staff from Nils and Arnaud at the concierge desk to the rest are completely committed to making your experience in Paris nothing less than special. Our rooms were beautifully appointed, comfortable, spotless, warm and cozy. The hotel was quiet but in the middle of the Marais which is an exceedingly lively part of town so it became our oasis. We will stay here anytime and everytime we are in Paris.

Stayed one night with my oldest son and enjoyed every minute
Place des Vosges is well situated, nice restaurants and close to much
Inside the hotel gate it is so peaceful and calm: exactly what one needs

The Pavillion de la Reine is a lovely, intimate boutique hotel tucked behind the cloisters in the Place des Vosges, a genuine Parisian neighborhood. It's very fashionable and tasteful, though not pretentious or grand. A very easy place to relax in. Very helpful staff. The lobby public rooms work as well any I have set foot in: they serve breakfast, aperitifs, dinner, lobby lounging very effectively. A beautiful courtyard is out front too. Standard rooms are nicely decorated, though the more contemporarily themed ones work better. They are small though. It's not a hotel for the claustraphobic. Still, it's got great atmosphere and one feels as though they are staying at a private club, versus a hotel.

A beautiful oasis, lovely furnished rooms with excellent toiletries and linens. Exceptionally gracious, thoughtful, knowledgeable concierges, Rudy and Arnaud. Breakfast has a generous assortment of food and very good service. Looking forward to our next stay here!

Wonderful hotel with excellent breakfast. Staff professional and friendly - the best of French hospitality.
Rooms small - as usual for Paris, Wonderful location in place des Vosges, Marais.
Hidden away, a sanctuary...

Happy to recommend this hotel. Excellent standard. Great staff, beautiful room/suite, and in a great location. It is set back from the Place des Vosges making it so quiet and relaxing to return to after a hectic day of discovering Paris! There are lots of cafes, bars, restaurants, bistros, boutiques, shops, metro right on your doorstep. It was perfect! (Hotel drinks - tea coffees etc were very expensive - which is why we chose to go out for breakfast - but you get what you pay for!!)

Gorgeous hotel in the heart of Place des Vosges in the Marais neighbourhood. Friendly and hospitable, staff are at hand to attend to your every whim. The rooms are uniquly designed, I had a suite which was generous in size with large bathroom, separate WC, large lounge area and bedroom. The breakfast was vast and super tasty. The spa was so relaxing and thoroughly recommended.

This was a super hotel, beutifully furnishes, extremely helpful staff and a cosy honesty bar for an evening drink. We didn't eat in the hotel or use the spa facilities but I imagine they are equally impressive. I would certainy stay here again.

I traveled alone to Paris (just because) - Stayed 6 nights at La Pavillon de la Reine; before I arrived, the hotel concierge staff (Arnaud & Rudy) were extremely responsive to several emails I sent, and they were able to obtain a ticket for me to a long-sold-out opera performance.

The hotel is beautiful and extremely quiet (a gorgeous courtyard between the main entrance and the famous, quiet square in which it is located). Public areas have gorgeous, sophisticated decor; I didn’t see other guest rooms, but mine was immaculate, spacious, bright, and very colorful - fantastic bathroom btw.

Morning breakfast buffet served in two quiet rooms off the main lobby is fantastic, with options to please anyone. Room service was prompt and extremely courteous (thank you, Mantie!). Also appreciated the evening honor bar in lobby.

I spent every day enjoying Paris, but at the end of all that, Le Pavillon de la Reine was a wonderful spot to come “home” to. The hotel is not inexpensive, but it is exceptional for those comfortable with the price.

Very nice and pleasant hotel at one of the loveliest places of Paris. Family hotel with good service and friendly staff. We would surely recommand this hotel and if possible we will be coming back to this hotel when we will visit Paris in the future.

Stayed with my wife and daughter and we all loved this hotel. Excellent location at Place de Vosges and in the hart of Le Marais. Friendly and personal staff, authentic rooms, a nice spa en fitness and parking. Concierge Fred made us feel very welcome and had great advice for our special night out. Will definitely come back!

Loved the hotel and will recommend it to anyone who want to visit Paris and stay in the Marais area. We picked it after much research since we were visiting Paris for longer than a week and we wanted a hotel with great service in a nice location. We were not disappointed. The hotel accommodated our needs excellently and we recommend you to work with the hotel on your needs. The staff was fantastic and were readily available. The property is pretty, the rooms are well done and comfortable and we did not feel any stress of staying in the same room for longer than a week. The hotel breakfast was a highlight and we looked forward to it everyday. The food in Restaurant 28 was of high quality.

In short, it is a great hotel and we highly recommend it.

Another wonderful stay. Service is personable and warm. If you need more room, the larger suites offer excellent value for Paris. Breakfast and the honor bar are both great. The location can't be beat. What's not to like?

I can't say enough good things about this hotel. Located within walking distance of most attactions, a fantastic spa and spacious room. But the best part was the staff. There wasn't a request, from tickets to museums to help with getting a vaccination pass to getting a knife to cut some cheese in our room that they didn't fulfill with a yes and a smile. I've never had such attentive treatment in any hotel I've stayed in and I've stayed in a lot. Will definitely be returning here!

The stay was simply awesome. Hotel, food, the friendliness made us feel home from the moment we entrerer the hotel. The breakfast was also really great and the dinner both in Anne and in No. 28 was truly excellent. Cannot wait to get back

.

I should start by saying the hotel seems much smaller in real life than the photos suggest, and of course this being Paris, the hotel rooms are quite small. However, it's a very nice hotel in a good location. The staff were very pleasant and everything went smoothly. Breakfast was also a nice selection, and we liked having the choice of different rooms to eat in, or weather permitting, to eat outside.

Our long weekend trip was packed so we didn't truly get to relax and enjoy the hotel to its full capacity. If I dare have one gripe it's the fact the rooms do have Smart TV's yet there's no Netflix and you will struggle to find an English language channel unless you want to only watch the news. This being France you can't even watch Amazon Prime on your own appliances. I appreciate you don't go away to watch TV, but after a day out and about, and a good dinner somewhere, watching TV in bed to end the day is one of life's little luxuries when travelling.

Place de Voges is very nice, though rather limited. It wasn't quite as chic as expected. But it's quiet and you can get a good nights sleep, and it's close to all the most important things you probably want to see.

Probably most importantly, we would stay at the hotel again.
.

This is our favourite hotel in Paris. It provides everything we want including an excellent location with easy access to the other parts of Paris we love. Its new restaurant, Anne, is worth visiting too. We were blown away by the quality of the food.

You can have the Crillon, the Ritz and the Place Vendome, but give me the Pavillon de la Reine, originally built in the 1600s for Louis XIII and his queen. Step out from the charming hotel into the Place des Vosge and enjoy pastry shops, bistros and art galleries all under the gothic arcades surrounding the leafy, arboreal square. Or go for a jog around the park and the school children at play. Besides it's chic and central location, it's a wonderful hotel. The decor is elegantly colorful and updated. The rooms are cozy, yet spacious The bathroom and amenities are top notch. My shower pressure was amazing! The staff was friendly expeditious, helpful and attitude free. Will return. Loved it.

Great hotel on the Place des Vosges. Couldn't ask for a better location. Good service and the people working there are all very nice. Room was beautiful and comfortable. Great location for a walking tour of all of Paris.

Always a favorite hotel. Love the location, and the staff is amazing and attentive. My room was beautiful and quiet. The area is fun with lots to do, and walkable is you want. Can't wait too go back!!

We loved our stay at this small hotel. It is located in the Marais area. So close to great shopping and food.

We were upgraded to a loft. Very spacious room.

The breakfast was great. Sorry that the restaurant was closed for evening meal.

We had a delightful time.

Would go back.

This is a hotel that gets every detail just right. It is elegant, but warm and gracious at the same time. The food was some of the best we had in Paris (and that is saying something). The concierge Arnaud was amazing before and during our stay. The location on the Place des Voges was unbeatable. We hated to leave and there is no other place we will stay in future trips to Paris.

We spent two nights here recently and found the staff, and service to be delightful, helpful, and very attentive. The hotel is beautifully situated on the right bank with so many great spots all around - shopping, restaurants, museums, etc. The breakfast is delicious and relaxing, and there is great food the rest of the day with an honor bar for the afternoon and evening.. The courtyard on a pretty day is delightful.
The two distractions for us were the exceedingly small, dark bedrooms and the tiny hallways and elevator. When shown our first room, we asked to be moved, and were given a room that was slightly better. There is no room for suitcases and with two people in the room we felt as if we were on top of each other. The decor is SO dark - black painted walls and doors, dark colored curtains and carpets, etc. And the lighting in the bedrooms is very dim despite there being sconces and lamps everywhere. It just felt like a basement room and did not have a refreshing feel. The hallways and elevator were very small also... like a doll house. Though the service was great, the tiny, dark rooms will prevent us from returning.

Everything about our stay was perfection. The location could not be better - across from the park in the center of the Marais, yet it's pin-drop quiet in a blissful courtyard; the breakfasts are amazing and the service is incredibly warm and helpful; the hotel is stylish and intimate, and the terrace is a great place to gather with friends. Best of all was the concierge services. I'd had the unfortunate luck of going to a bad hair salon (not recommended by the hotel) the night before an important work event; it was late at night on a Sunday. The amazing concierge went above and beyond and called every person in her rolodex and somehow miraculously found a fabulous hair stylist to come to our room at 10pm to fix my hair - I was astounded. Another concierge helped me find all of the flea market information and reviews, and another helped with gallery exhibitions. Throughout our stay, the staff was helpful, warm, welcoming, and resourceful. The concierge staff at this hotel should teach a master class. We felt incredibly well cared for throughout our wonderful 8-day stay.

We hope to return soon and often.

If I could change one thing it would be the room size (this is central Paris - to be expected) - our initial room was small (and had limited place for clothing); but they were able to change us to a different room with much more space. The WIFI was a bit iffy at times, but I hear that they are working on this.

What an amazing place to stay in Paris. Centrally located and impeccable service. My wife and I were celebrating our wedding anniversary with a trip to Paris and this was the perfect hotel to choose. All the staff were very helpful, courteous and knowledgeable.

Superb location, service and amenities.
Went there as a couple but also suitable for a family.
Concierge was really helpful.
Outdoor patio is outstanding.
Rooms were big enough for a Parisian Hotel. Would repeat, no doubt

The location of the hotel is perfect, tucked away in a picturesque courtyard. What made our trip was the hotel staff, especially Fred! He was super helpful, helping us arrange reservations and gave us amazing recommendations.
We cant wait to come back!!

This is a beautiful gem of a hotel. The staff are wonderful - nothing is too much trouble. They make the hotel special. They were friendly efficient and helpful. Our room overlooked the beautiful vine clad courtyard where we also enjoyed excellent breakfasts. Location is perfect too - super quiet but close to everything.
Highly recommend.

Great hotel in the middle of a bustling central part of Paris. Very friendly and helpful staff. Absolutely recommend it. We stayed with a family of five and even the kids loved it. The garden outside particularly is very pleasant o stay and relax.

Fabulous small hotel in the Marais, close to everything and right off the Places de Voges. The staff was attentive and the hotel has an intimate, luxurious feel. The food was fantastic and the wine list exeptional.

You feel like royalty when staying in this hotel. From the second the porter rushes out to get your luggage, the service is 5-star and continues to be. The restaurant and courtyard are lovely and the food delicious. The location is excellent and the gorgeous Place de Vosges is a beautiful morning stroll to get whatever you need to go. The beds are comfortable and the air conditioning actually works (unlike most European hotels, where it's minimal). I would highly recommend it and will stay again.

Perfect location!! Right opposite one of the most beautiful parks in Paris, Place des Vosges. So many amazing restaurants, boutiques and museums in the area. I loved that I could walk to so many places. The hotel is in a very quiet street and very beautiful with all the vines growing on the building. Great breakfast selection and I love the access to the gym, jacuzzi and spa. We used the jacuzzi and had it reserved to ourselves for 1 hour due to covid rules, which we loved. For a small boutique hotel it has a lot of great ammenities. Highly recommend this hotel in my favourite neighbourhood in Paris.

We loved our stay at this beautiful boutique hotel. The staff went out of their way to make our stay as comfortable as possible. The hotel breathes a true Parisian vibe and the complimentary valet parking added to the experience.

We loved our staying in this peaceful chateau. Staff was very friendly and the facilities were great too.
The restaurant food was amazing. We loved the bbq options too. Not to mention about the nature around the place

We stayed here for one night last week and wished it could have been longer. A lovely hotel in a lovely busy neighborhood of Paris. Our room was on the top floor, and had all the expected comforts. The staff was gracious and accommodating, preparing our room quickly. We enjoyed champagne on the terrace, dinner in the hotel restaurant and a wonderful breakfast in bed before our departure. I would not hesitate to recommend this beautiful hotel.

PDLR is the perfect hotel for a quiet, restful stay in Paris - in the heart of the bustling Marais. Service is great, and while limited by Covid guidelines for certain services, overall the hotel was able to remain accommodating and hospitable for requests. Great concierge service that helped me repair my suitcase same day, arrange for a Rapid Covid Test to be conducted in the comfort of my room, and of course - all general restaurant reservation and museum tickets, etc. I'll be coming back!

I stayed here for a relaxing weekend away with my mother in fall 2019. The hotel is absolutely gorgeous. I particularly loved the breakfast they offered in the hotel's cosy dining room. The location, on the Place des Vosges, has great shopping and culture. It is the perfect location to offer you a glimpse of true Parisian life, while also having lots to do. The hotel is adjacent to the Marais, a wonderful district in Paris. It is also near many museums and just a short drive from other big Paris sites.

We were lucky enough to stay here just before lockdown began. We had a lovely room which was beautifully decorated. We settled in immediately.... the hotel was also very accommodating over dietary issues which is always tricky in France! We met many guest who where hotel regulars (fashion week) which is always a good sign.The only negative was the shower no bath in the room but I hadn't checked before. I will definitely stay here again.

This is a beautiful property in a wonderful part of Paris. The rooms are fine, not that large, but they are very well appointed. The hallways are quite dark and dingy, with low ceilings. Elevators are tiny and quite old as well. I wanted to like the hotel but from the beginning, when I entered the property, I didn't feel well taken care of or as if the staff even wanted me there as a guest. I didn't find the service for breakfast to be helpful or friendly either. Next time I come to Paris I would probably choose another hotel or just stay in an Air BNB as I usually do in Paris.

My favourite thing about this hotel is the private courtyard and honesty bar. At night the gates close and you are free to linger over drinks on the pretty, ivy clad terrace until late. Rooms are varied, the one I stayed in was nothing to write home about but the ambiance overall is charming and the location is perfect.

My stay at the Pavillon de la Reine was a long time coming and it didn't fail or disappoint. Perfectly located to access many of the Marias' charming cafes and bistros and super stylish shops and boutiques as well as countless museums. The hotel is so beautiful, hidden away in a quiet courtyard, you would harldy know you were in a city. Beautiful inside with warm cosy interiors, the hote is bursting with country-style touches and oodles of charm. Breakfast is absolutely outstanding with a very wide choice to keep even the fussy eater happy. The hotel has an honesty bar stocked with many drinks. I wouldn't hesitate to stay here again,

This is our second stay at Le Pavillon. We have been visiting the Marais for about 20 years and the location can't be beat. We opted for a larger suit this time and were not disappointed. The staff is very helpful and made all our dinner reservations. During the strike they kept us updated on all transportation issues. Just made reservations for our next visit.

If you are looking for a refined, elegant hotel near Le Marais, this is it. The Hotel decor is elegant and refined without being stuffy. The patio, lobby and dining areas are welcoming and intimate. There is a open, honor bar off the lobby stocked with quality wine, champagne and spirits for a drink with friends all afternoon and evening.

My room was truly memorable, which is saying a lot given how much I travel. It was beautifully decorated with open beam ceilings and deep set character windows overlooking the streets below. It had a comfortable and lovely living room area, well appointed bath, and large bedroom with period antique furniture.

The staff at the front desk was very helpful and friendly.

My only criticism is that the support staff could be better trained. In the middle of a business breakfast I was holding in the dining room, one of the support staff decided to vacuum the room around us. Which made our business conversation impossible and raised dust around our meal. I did mention something to the front desk and hopefully that will be rectified in the future.

But it all this hotel is highly recommended and a beautiful find in the heart of Paris.

On our previous visits to Paris, including for our honeymoon, we stayed at the charming luxury boutique Hôtel Duc de Saint-Simon located in the 6th arrondissement in St. Germain-Des-Pres. For this trip, however, we decided to check out Le Marais, the very hip and colorful district straddling the 3rd and 4th arrondissements. A savvy traveler friend directed us to the five-star hotel Le Pavillon de la Reine, located on the Place des Vosges, in the center of it all.

This regal stone and brick structure beckoned visitors through a narrow passageway leading into a lovely courtyard with umbrellaed tables surrounded by greenery fronting the hotel’s main entrance. Given the season, it was festively lit prompting many passersby to sate their Instagram addictions. The lobby and common rooms were tastefully decorated and furnished, though a bit subdued for my taste. The words “cozy, “classic” and “quaint” come to mind.

We reasoned it was a five-star hotel (with a five-star rack rate), so little need to book the honeymoon suite. Any room would be special. Right? We soon squeezed into the small lift and were led to our “classic” room, which was just over the hotel‘s entrance overlooking the courtyard. It was duplex connected by a steep, narrow staircase. The bedroom was in the loft and below it was a small sitting space and the bathroom. Between the two spaces, we had barely enough room for our two suitcases, packed for ten days on the road, and very little shelving or closet space. We also soon realized that the opening and closing of the hotel’s front door did not bode well for light sleepers.

The next morning, we requested a room change, which the hotel graciously obliged. The “superior” room to which they moved us, was in the back and much quieter, but it was even smaller than the first. Oh well. We’re only sleeping here one more night. That said, the bed was comfy and the hotel’s location at Place des Vosges unmatched.

It's a treat to stay at PDLR! Everyone is helpful and eager to please. The rooms are spacious for Paris, and the location can't be beat. The courtyard is the perfect setting for a late-night cocktails. It's also a nice place to unwind after a day of museum-hopping. An oasis in the middle of Paris's bustling street life.

Beautiful boutique hotel in the historic Place de Vosges. Enter through a traditional Paris gate/door into a magical courtyard. Wonderful staff. Beautiful, comfortable, quiet sitting room in the entrance. There is a spa but we didn’t visit.
We stayed in one of the cheaper rooms so it was small and beside the elevator but it was still very comfortable and the bathroom was very nice. Clean. Welcome chocolate too! I just can’t give 5 stars for a place that costs this much! Other than price - no complaints.

This lovely hotel offers comfort, delightful service and discreet luxury in a beautiful setting. It is wonderfully located and once you have stayed here you will always want to return. In short, it is special.

As a guest of usually large corporate luxury properties, my husband and I were excited to try a smaller bespoke boutique and we couldn't have been more pleased with our decision. Everything from the location, decor and amenities were beyond perfect but it was the staff that truly made our stay. Le Pavilion de la Reine's amazing team assisted us with VIP airport pick up and drop off during the transportation strike, helped us discover new restaurants and secure the perfect reservation times as well as just their overall demeanor of always going above and beyond was TOP KNOTCH, we cannot recommend this hotel enough to family, friends and strangers alike. It was the perfect spot to kick off our honeymoon and made us feel so welcome and at home.

I stayed here for one night only when my train to Strasbourg was cancelled due to the strike. Stayed 5 other nights at Hotel Luxembourg Parc ( see separate review). This is a very nice hotel on one of the most beautiful squares in Paris. Room was a bit small ( and I didn’t book the smallest option) but nicely decorated and fine for one person. Would have been tight for more. What makes this hotel are the location and really helpful professional staff. Although I only stayed one night I felt well taken care of and found everyone charming and very helpful. There is a lovely place to sit outside in good weather and the bar and restaurant are both very appealing. The location, close to so many things yet quietly set off the square is very special.

Have stayed at this hotel for the past five years or so. Cannot recommend it highly enough. Every thing here works really really well in a way that immediately makes you feel at home. The staff, rooms and food are all simply outstanding. Moreover the excellence is both consistent and sustained.

I am traveling a lot around the globe. Clearly Le Pavillon de la Reine (PdlR) is one of the top 3 hotels in Paris! The entire package is consistent at the highest level. Food excellent, accommodation top notch and above the service conveys an unmatched notion of greatest hospitality. No matter if you are young or old, single or couple, male or female this hotel matches everybody's expectations before you are even aware of your expectations! First choice! Love it! Looking forward to my next stay! Thank you to the whole PdlR Team!

I stayed for one night in the family suite, it is a 2 bedrooms suite with a cozy salon and 3 bathrooms! Very clean, spacious rooms, and a very generous and tasty breakfast. They even have a chemney!!
Me and my family had a very pleasing experience, and we surely recommend le pavillon de la reine

My 18 year old daughter and I couldn't have been happier at this boutique hotel for a long weekend. We absolutely loved the Marais area and enjoyed seeing this part of Paris that was not as touristy. We went to 4 great restaurants while we were there -- Monjul, Le Sergent Recruteur, Le Petit Marche and Chez Janou. All were great. The first two were more fine dining and the last two more casual. We had a great walking tour with Richard Nahem who showed us his "home" of the Marais district. Breakfast at the hotel included yogurt, pastries and fresh fruit. A perfect start to the day. The rooms are beautiful but small. They use every square inch but they do it well. Having been to Paris before, anyone who says the Parisians are not polite and kind did not have the experience we had. Everyone we encountered at the hotel, the restaurants, and the shops were very hospitable. Would 100% recommend this hotel to anyone!

Great little hotel, beautifully placed at Place de Vosges. Staff is friendly and attentive. I love the self-serve Honesty-Bar were You help Yourself and write a note of what You have taken. Makes it all very relaxed. The furniture is not the best for having breakfast, but great for drinks in the afternoon.

My wife and I stayed here for 2 nights and it was a very beautiful hotel. The location is quite central with many cafes and shops nearby. We had a room which faced the courtyard which was nice and gave us ample sunshine.

It can get a little noisy as it is next to a side alley where many cars and scooters use as well as many students access it to walk to the park across the road.

Like most hotels in Paris the room is small so for two people and two large luggage it is a little tight. The air conditioning was a bit weak especially if we left the curtain opened.

Overall a nice hotel and a pleasant stay.

My husband and I loved this hotel. It is in the most beautiful location. We stayed there twice in September. The staff were amazing - the concierge and front desk brilliant. Our two rooms - we stayed twice in a week were outstanding. We booked a Junior suite both times and it was beautiful. When we retuned after a few days we were upgraded to the Victor Hugo suite - superb.
This is the best hotel we have stayed in in Paris - understated elegant and SO comfortable. We want to return!

I booked this hotel for it's decor and location, but I was thoroughly impressed with it's service and amenities. While our room was not large, it was so well thought out that it never felt cluttered or overcrowded. Room service keeps things impeccable, and when they accidentally dropped a perfume sample (not a full bottle even), management sent us a handwritten note and a box of macarons despite the in person apology we had already received from housekeeping. The concierge was also extremely helpful with restaurants. Everything served at breakfast is of excellent quality. Overall, service is smooth, professional and very pleasant. We didn't have the time for a spa treatment but really enjoyed a quick visit to the jacuzzi and steam room which were top notch. I wouldn't hesitate to stay here again or recommend it to friends.

This hotel is located in a bustling neighborhood of restaurants and shops actoss from a park. The service was perfect and the hotel had a number of cozy commonn rooms to eat a nice breakfast (provided) or an after dinner drink. A quiet patio was also a nice place to spend time on sunny days.

From the moment I set foot in Le Pavilion until I checked out the service was impeccable. Probably equal to or better than the best hotels I’ve visited. My room was very comfortable and attractive. I did change from the first one I was shown because I felt it was small for the price, even for Paris. The front desk couldn’t have been more pleasant or accommodating. I love the location in the Marais and this is the first time I’ve stayed there. My other visits to Paris I’ve always stayed in the 6th arrondissement. I will definitely return to Le Pavilion de la Reine.

It is a beautiful hotel with relaxed atmosphere and wonderful hospitality. My husband and I stayed 2 nights, we loved walking around the hotel visiting galleries and nightcap in the beautiful garden after our excursion. The room was very nicely decorated with lovely flower bouquet in a vase on a coffee table. Breakfast was good too. It would have been perfect if there were better quality pillows (the bed was fairly comfortable) and better WiFi. We will definitely go back.

Quite simply the best. The service from the staff made our stay so easy and the quality of the hotel, its food and drink is just unmatched. It is not possible to be disappointed. We were celebrating our 40th wedding anniversary and they were so helpful in assisting us as we prepared for a "re-do" of our vows.

We stayed for 4 nights to start our honeymoon and were very impressed by the property overall.

The location is really the stand-out. We’d never been to Le Marais before, and now, plan to only stay in this neighborhood. So much history and charm, with great shopping and restaurants nearby.

The hotel itself was beautiful and the staff were great. I do wish they’d acknowledged our honeymoon, but I know that’s not something you can really expect. We did get wine and a $100 credit due to booking with American Express, but did not get a room upgrade. Our room was very small, and the bathroom configuration was quite odd (toilet right behind the door). The elevator and hallways were narrow and small as well.

I had a massage one day which the hotel was able to arrange very minute for me; it was great. Only downside was that there were no spa amenities available for use, so it was just the massage.

We had breakfast onsite twice and it was quite good, albeit expensive.

Overall, great stay, and we wouldn’t hesitate to stay here again - but would pay for a larger room.

The hotel is in a beautiful location and within easy walking distance of excellent cafés, bars and restaurants. During our four-night stay, the atmosphere throughout the Pavillon was one of calm and elegance. Our room was quiet and comfortable, overlooking a small central courtyard of trees. The service was first class in every respect. From the receptionists, through the concierges, to the staff who served us at breakfast and at the tables in the charming front courtyard, everyone was courteous, friendly, professional and helpful. In our experience, larger five-star hotels can be impersonal: here, the staff regularly greeted us by name and were generous with their time when we had requests or inquiries.
